{"number":"01","directions":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <title>Arduino Lesson</title>\n  <style>\n    body {\n      font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\n      color: #222;\n      background: #fafafa;\n      line-height: 1.6;\n      margin: 0;\n      padding: 20px;\n    }\n    h1, h2 {\n      margin-top: 1em;\n    }\n    h1 {\n      font-size: 1.6em;\n    }\n    h2 {\n      font-size: 1.2em;\n      border-bottom: 2px solid #ccc;\n      padding-bottom: 0.3em;\n    }\n    .code {\n      font-family: monospace;\n      background: #f5f5f5;\n      padding: 2px 5px;\n      border-radius: 4px;\n    }\n    details {\n      margin: 1em 0;\n      padding: 0.8em;\n      border: 1px solid #ccc;\n      border-radius: 6px;\n      background: #fff;\n    }\n    details summary {\n      font-weight: bold;\n      color: #0073e6;\n      cursor: pointer;\n    }\n    .description {\n      margin-top: 0.6em;\n      padding-left: 1em;\n      border-left: 3px solid #ddd;\n      font-style: italic;\n      color: #444;\n    }\n    ol {\n      margin-left: 1.5em;\n    }\n    .activities li {\n      margin-bottom: 0.6em;\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n  <h1>A program that does nothing.</h1>\n\n  <details>\n    <summary>NEW: <span class=\"code\">void setup()</span></summary>\n    <div class=\"description\">\n      <strong>DESCRIPTION:</strong> <br>\n      setup runs <strong>only once</strong> under these conditions:\n      <ol>\n        <li>When the Arduino is turned on</li>\n        <li>When the Arduino is reset (find the reset button)</li>\n        <li>When downloading a program and resetting the Arduino</li>\n        <li>D13 flashes 3 times to indicate successful reset</li>\n      </ol>\n    </div>\n  </details>\n\n  <details>\n    <summary>NEW: <span class=\"code\">pinMode(2, OUTPUT);</span></summary>\n    <div class=\"description\">\n      Enables pin 2 on the Arduino to send enough power to turn on an LED.  \n      Usage: Arduino may now turn on the LED at pin 2, but this does not actually turn it on.  \n      For that, you need: <span class=\"code\">digitalWrite(2, HIGH);</span>\n    </div>\n  </details>\n\n  <details>\n    <summary>NEW: <span class=\"code\">void loop()</span></summary>\n    <div class=\"description\">\n      <span class=\"code\">loop()</span> runs <strong>over and over forever</strong> after <span class=\"code\">setup()</span> finishes.\n    </div>\n  </details>\n\n  <details>\n    <summary>NEW: <span class=\"code\">delay(5000);</span></summary>\n    <div class=\"description\">\n      Tells Arduino to wait 5000ms (5 seconds) before going to the next instruction.\n    </div>\n  </details>\n\n  <h2>Activities</h2>\n  <ol class=\"activities\">\n    <li>Copy the program from <em>Starting Point Exercise01</em> into the Arduino IDE. Compile and upload.</li>\n    <li>Verify that no LEDs light up.</li>\n    <li>Save the sketch as <strong>YourInitials_Exercise01</strong> in <code>Documents → Arduino → Exercises</code>.</li>\n    <li>Copy the code into the <a href=\"http://dpengineering.github.io/giffer-reborn/\" target=\"_blank\">Giffer</a> website.</li>\n    <li>Enter your <em>name</em> and <em>exercise number</em>.</li>\n    <li>Select <i>Run and Grade</i>.</li>\n    <li>Check output image shows <span style=\"color: green;\"><strong>Correct</strong></span>.</li>\n    <li>If Correct, use the <strong>Copy Page</strong> button to copy evidence.</li>\n    <li>Upload evidence to <strong>CL 10.3.01 Upload Completed Exercise01</strong>.</li>\n    <li>On Canvas, click “Prepare an answer” → “&lt;&gt;” (Source code) → paste with CTRL+V.</li>\n    <li><strong>Submit</strong></li>\n    <li>If you changed code in Giffer, copy it back to Arduino and re-save as <em>YourInitials_Exercise01</em>.</li>\n  </ol>\n\n</body>\n</html>\n","startingCode":"void setup()\n{\n  pinMode(2, OUTPUT); // Enables pin 2 on the Arduino to Send enough power (current) \n                                       // to turn on LED attached to pin 2}\n}\n\nvoid loop()\n{\n   delay(5000);  // wait 5000ms or 5 seconds before going to the next line\n}\n","suffix":"int main() {\n  setup();\n  loop();\n  return 0;\n}\n","board":{"type":"LED Board","setup":{"pinKeyframes":[]}},"frameManager":{"frames":[{"ledModes":{"2":1},"ledStates":{"2":1023},"postDelay":5000,"outputText":[]},{"ledModes":{"2":1},"ledStates":{"2":1023},"postDelay":0,"outputText":[]}],"currentFrame":1,"elapsedTime":5000,"isGraded":true,"grade":false}}